name: Enameled Platter With Dome Lid
description:
Once used to serve tantalizing meals, this enameled lidded platter features a black exterior with drizzled paint and a solid white interior. This gently used vintage product is in good condition.

L 15” W 12.50” H 5”

name: Art Deco Style Vase
description:
This beautiful Art Deco vase was made in the 1930s and is an excellent example of Bauhaus pottery—a short-lived but highly influential movement. Marked “Made in Belgium.” Used. 1 small chip, minor age crazing throughout

L 5.75” W 6” H 6.25”

name: Enamelware Bait Pail
description:
This enameled bait pail was originally used to house a range of squirmy, slimy things that fish love to chomp. This pail includes a handle, lid, and feet. This vintage product is in fair, “as found” condition. The pail is aged, with rust and wear to enamel.

H 6.75” D 10.25”

name: Malted Milk Mixer
description:
This vintage glass malt mixer features a metal cap and plunger, as well as measurements in ounces. The mixer holds 12oz and features what appears to be an “AH” mark on the bottom. Both the glass and metal cap have patent information on them. This gently used vintage product is in good condition. The metal has a patina and a bit of wear to it, while the glass body is in perfect condition, with no chips, nicks, or cracks.

H 9.50” D 3"

name: Chevron Chochet Throw
description:
Hand Made chevron crochet throw in a vibrant  yellow and orange.
